  "prompt": "What is the best crowdfunding platform for a B2B project?",
  "response": "Several crowdfunding platforms are suitable for B2B projects, each with unique strengths:\n\n1. Kickstarter\n- Popular for innovative products\n- Strong tech and design community\n- High visibility\n- Requires reaching full funding goal\n\n2. Indiegogo\n- More flexible funding options\n- Lower barrier to entry\n- Good for hardware and tech projects\n- International reach\n\n3. SeedInvest\n- Specifically for equity crowdfunding\n- Focused on startups and B2B ventures\n- Accredited investor network\n- More rigorous screening process\n\n4. Fundable\n- Specifically designed for B2B startups\n- Allows reward and equity-based funding\n- Business-focused community\n- Straightforward process\n\n5. StartEngine\n- Equity crowdfunding platform\n- Supports various business stages\n- SEC-registered\n- Good for tech and innovation projects\n\n6. Republic\n- Startup and small business focused\n- Offers equity and token offerings\n- Diverse investor base\n- Strong due diligence\n\nBest choice depends on:\n- Project type\n- Funding goals\n- Target audience\n- Specific platform requirements\n\nRecommend researching each platform's specific terms and success rates for your particular project.",
